%N A221448 Number of 3 X n binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1.
%H A221448 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A221448/b221448.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A221448 <a href="/index/Rec#order_17">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,8,46,39,69,-10,-38,-68,-40,50,18,-13,-7,4,2,-1,1).
%F A221448 Empirical: a(n) = 5*a(n-1) +8*a(n-2) +46*a(n-3) +39*a(n-4) +69*a(n-5) -10*a(n-6) -38*a(n-7) -68*a(n-8) -40*a(n-9) +50*a(n-10) +18*a(n-11) -13*a(n-12) -7*a(n-13) +4*a(n-14) +2*a(n-15) -a(n-16) +a(n-17).
%F A221448 The above empirical formula confirmed using the transfer matrix method. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 18 2026
